        "🪞 Echoes of self-reflection bounce off the shell."
        "🪞 You are not your \$USER. But it’s a start."
        "🪞 The prompt knows more than you think."
        "🪞 The shell is just the surface — dig deeper."
        "🪞 If you don't know your \$0, how can you run anything?"
        "🪞 Variables reflect your choices — make them global with care."
        "🪞 The login prompt asks who you are — answer honestly."
        "🪞 Debug the self before debugging the script."
        "🪞 You cannot grep for truth unless you log it first."
        "🪞 \$HOME  is not your true home — but it’s close."
        "🪞 Even root must face the mirror."

        # ⚖️ Nothing in Excess
        "⚖️ Too many flags spoil the command."
